The course develops all the aspects of the language: reading, listening, writing, speaking in order to reach the B1 level of the CEFR.Objectives/eesmärkid:  to develop students' English language skills so that by the end of the course they would reach the B1 level of the Common European Framework of Reference for Languages.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1) knows and is able to use essential vocabulary at B1 level 2) knows and is able to use the main grammatical structures of English 3) can write a simple connected text on a familiar topic 4) can understand the content of everyday conversations, radio or TV programmes and connected texts, which consist of more frequent vocabulary and structures 5) is able to hold a conversation on a familiar or important topic (e.g. family, hobbies, work, travelling, etc.).
